article.headline: Dayton 73, Florida A&M 48
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Brian Roberts had 20 points and eight assists to lead Dayton to a 73-48 win over Florida A&M on Monday night. Norman Plummer had 13 points and Jimmy Binnie added 12 for the Flyers (8-3), who outscored the Rattlers 44-29 in the second half to expand on a 10-point halftime lead. Dayton led by as many as 31 points. Joe Ballard had 10 points and four rebounds for the Rattlers (3-6), whose only lead was at 9-8. Florida A&M had 17 turnovers, leading to 22 Dayton points. The Flyers shot 42.4 percent from the floor while holding the Rattlers to 31.4 percent. The game was Florida A&M's third in Ohio this season. The Rattlers beat Cleveland State 68-66 on Nov. 19 and fell to Xavier 79-51 on Dec. 7.
